This paper focuses on the analysis of a real-world network, specifically Southwest Airlines' domestic route service, using subgraphs and motifs. The paper discusses the dynamic and spatial properties of small undirected subgraphs and proposes a subgraph-based node ranking measure. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
